The focus of the four-day course is to impart practical knowledge on the management of musculoskeletal trauma, according to a statement released by MOI.It was noted that the course utilised a combination of case-based work and hands-on skill sessions by both orthopaedic and plastic surgeons who teach core principles in fracture management and soft-tissue reconstruction. This year s course covers module on upper extremity, pelvis and acetabulum pathway, and deformity.Hands-on surgical exposure to these procedures is the main focus of the course using cadaver labs as well as case-based discussions of the attendee s submitted cases, part of the statement reads.